* D rolled his eyes. Had these people never seen flesh?
But, he did suppose a bit that these beings who seemed to be made of metal 
could know nothing of humans or the ones he had come with.
He clawed the ground slightly and growled with frustration, his limited 
speach made this so hard!*

" Flesh...beings."

* That didn't sounds right either! It was proper, yes, but it wasn't really 
what he was trying to say! D's voice had been gruff and it was no better 
with his frustration.*

" Urr....being flesh...hu...hum..an flesh?"

* It was more as if he was talking to himself in order to see if he had 
gotten it right. Hu-man, that sounded like it. That was what his keepers 
were. Hu-mans.
D looked Fenox in the face, his nose less then two inches from her own.*

" Hu-man flesh, where?"

* That was good enough. Thouth it was supposed to be Where is hu-man flesh? 
But he thought he had done pretty good.
He just hoped that this female could understand.*
